President Uhuru Kenyatta has eulogised Nyamira Governor John Nyagarama as a distinguished and true servant of the Kenyan people.
Nyagarama died early on Friday at the Nairobi Hospital. He was 74 years old.
In a condolence message to the family, the President described Nyagarama as a friendly, approachable, wise, witty and kind leader whose contribution to the country's progress, especially in the tea sector, will be remembered.



