“I have learnt with profound shock and sadness of the death of [the governor]. My family and I, and the national government send our deepest condolences and sympathies to the family and Nyamira residents," he said.
“As a nation, death has robbed us of a gifted leader whose primary mission was to transform the lives of residents of Nyamira through development initiatives,” he added.



