“We've lost a purpose-driven and consistent leader whose relentless pursuit of success saw him rise steadily, over the years, from a classroom teacher to one of our country's top leaders," he said.
"Nyagarama's unique ability to understand the challenges of his people and his strong work ethic propelled him to the high echelons of our country's leadership, rising to become the first governor of Nyamira County," the President said.
He prayed for comfort and fortitude for the county chief's family and the people of Nyamira.
Ruto's message
Via Twitter, Deputy President William Ruto said Nyagarama was a "selfless and formidable champion for devolution, who was genuinely dedicated to public service".
DP Ruto further described the governor as progressive, steadfast, responsive, industrious, focused and firm.
"He will be remembered as a leader who built a better, more inclusive and more transformed Nyamira," he said. His family says he had difficulty breathing after his lungs collapsed. Interior Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang'i was among leaders who went to Lee Funeral Home to condole with the family. His family says he had difficulty breathing after his lungs collapsed. Interior Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang'i was among leaders who went to Lee Funeral Home to condole with the family.